body: Hi guys,  I am having problems in the new version of honeybee with a material that I had previously added to the honeybee library (see the following discussion).  [http://www.grasshopper3d.com/group/ladybug/forum/topics/simulation-...](http://www.grasshopper3d.com/group/ladybug/forum/topics/simulation-of-microshade-using-honeybee?xg_source=activity) The thing is that this material that I added to the library is messing the new version of HB. I have reinstalled everythink (radiance, lh and hb) and the problem is still there. How can I delete this material from the library? [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/17W2v0xf-z*EzfDxL9tz2QSa0GlGbz*TxNHPelNTwoqRC8CGdpJqYwtQj-owtQ29V30UlwEg7BgA30AwMm8cYVkmEIOK64Kn/Capture.JPG) Thanks in advance! Ale
topic: Problems with the new version of HB

replies.body:
Hi Alejandro,



They are in a file named HoneybeeRadMaterials.mat. You can find it under the Ladybug default folder. Can you share your file with me so I can see why the files is failing to import? Do you have a new line between each material?



Mostapha

Hi Mostapha, 

Indeed, there was no empty line between the materials. I added it and now it works. 

Thanks!

Ale
